Package: importABCatlas
Title: Import Allen Brain Cell Atlas Data into R as Seurat Objects
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Uday", "Rangaswamy",  role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Federico", "Caretti", role = c("aut")))
Description: Provides an R-native interface to the Allen Brain Cell (ABC) Atlas.
    Wraps the 'abc_atlas_access' Python package via 'reticulate' to download and
    assemble cell metadata for supported datasets (whole human brain, whole mouse
    brain, aging mouse, and others) and to fetch gene expression for filtered
    cell populations as sparse 'Seurat' objects, enabling downstream single-cell
    analysis in R without Python or high-performance computing infrastructure.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
SystemRequirements: Python (>= 3.8), provisioned automatically by reticulate
    (via uv) on first use; an internet connection is required the first time.
Imports:
    dplyr,
    Matrix,
    reticulate (>= 1.41),
    Seurat,
    stats,
    tools
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
